An audit has revealed ghost projects were funded through the Kitui Rural National Government Constituency Development Fund.The report seen by the Star shows millions were paid for nonexistent projects.The projects management committees for Kwa Vonza chief camp Sh400,000 pit latrine project, Keseuni Chief&rsquo;s off Sh450,000 and a Sh400,000 classroom project at Kivunga Primary school got money for non-existent projects.The report indicates that although Sh1.6 million was paid out for the Kitui Rural Sports tournament, the audit could not conclusively establish if the tournament took place. It further points outs that Sh108,850 for building a single dustbin was an exaggeration.